                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00 Revolution 1931/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Funchal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Huddleston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-11T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 11, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram April 10, 4 p.m. The Department has been caused no embarrassment of
                    which it is aware and perceives no reason why an apology should be
                    necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
